50|$|<b>Azidamfenicol</b> is an amphenicol antibiotic, {{which has}} similar profile to chloramphenicol. It is used only topically, as eye drops and {{ointment}} {{for treatment of}} susceptible bacterial infections.|$|E
50|$|Examples of amphenicols include chloramphenicol, thiamphenicol, <b>azidamfenicol</b> and florfenicol. The first-in-class {{compound}} was chloramphenicol, {{introduced in}} 1949. Chloramphenicol was initially discovered {{as a natural}} product, but all amphenicols are now made by chemical synthesis.|$|E

